# ── Python ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ── Streamlit ───────────────────────────────────────────────
.streamlit/secrets.toml
streamlit.log

# ── Local settings & secrets (per-machine, may hold credentials) ────
.claude/settings.local.json
settings.local.json
*.local.json

# ── Personal / generated data (not needed to run the app) ───
# LinkedIn drafts & strategy — personal content, no code depends on it
linkedin/
# Claude Pro usage data — generated by the daily agent, degrades gracefully if absent
reports/*.json
# Runtime logs
logs/

# ── Call recorder — large binaries & temp transcripts ───────
call-recorder/model/
call-recorder/transcripts/
call-recorder/transcript_*.txt
call-recorder/recordings/

# ── OS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── IDE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/

# ── VAULT / SENSITIVE HR DATA — NEVER COMMIT (PUBLIC REPO) ───
# The Obsidian vault (TechColab_D&A_KO) is a SEPARATE, local-only repo synced
# via OneDrive. Its data (team profiles, stakeholders, PDIs, performance,
# compensation) must NEVER enter this PUBLIC repo. Defensive patterns:
*OneDrive*/
**/TechColab_D&A_KO/**
**/Stakeholders/**
**/1on1/
*_1on1_*.md
**/PDI.md
**/OKR.md
**/Overview.md
*Performance Assessment*
*Assessment Observations*
# NOTE: "backlog/" here is CODE. The vault's "backlog items/" is DATA → ignore it:
backlog items/

# Preview/dev server logs
preview-*.log
